---
import GuideLayout from "../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "How much does a final exam affect your grade?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "It depends on the weight of the final exam. A final worth 20% has a moderate impact, while a final worth 40% or more can significantly change your grade."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can a final exam raise your grade?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. A strong final exam score can raise your overall grade, especially if the final is heavily weighted."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can a final exam lower your grade?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. If your final exam score is lower than your current average, it can bring your overall grade down."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<GuideLayout
  title="How Finals Affect Your Grade (With Real Examples)"
  description="Learn how final exams impact your grade. See real examples and calculate your final outcome instantly."
  slug="/how-finals-affect-your-grade"
  heroTitle="How Finals Affect Your Grade"
  heroText="Your final exam can have a big impact on your grade, but how much it affects you depends on its weight and your current average."
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
>
  <div class="card">
    <p>
      Many students ask:
      <strong> “Will my final help or hurt my grade?” </strong>
      The answer depends on how much your final is worth and how well you perform.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>What Determines the Impact of Your Final?</h2>

    <p>
      The biggest factor is the <strong>weight of your final exam</strong>.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>10% final → small impact</li>
      <li>20% final → moderate impact</li>
      <li>30–40% final → major impact</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      The higher the weight, the more your final can change your overall grade.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Example 1: Final Raises Your Grade</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Current grade: 85%</li>
      <li>Final exam weight: 20%</li>
      <li>Final exam score: 95%</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Your final grade will increase because your exam score is higher than your
      current average.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Example 2: Final Lowers Your Grade</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Current grade: 85%</li>
      <li>Final exam weight: 20%</li>
      <li>Final exam score: 70%</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Your final grade will decrease because your exam score is lower than your
      current average.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Simple Formula</h2>

    <p>Final Grade =</p>

    <p>
      (Current Grade × Remaining Weight) + (Final Exam Score × Final Weight)
    </p>

    <p>
      This formula shows how both parts combine to create your final grade.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Use a Calculator (Faster & Easier)</h2>

    <p>
      Instead of calculating this manually, use the tool below:
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/final-exam-calculator">Final Exam Calculator</a>
    </p>

    <p>
      You can also figure out what score you need:
      <a href="/what-grade-do-i-need-calculator"> What Grade Do I Need Calculator</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Big Takeaway</h2>

    <p>
      Your final exam doesn’t automatically help or hurt your grade. It
      <strong> pulls your grade toward your exam score</strong>.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Score higher than your average → grade goes up</li>
      <li>Score lower than your average → grade goes down</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How much does a final affect your grade?</h3>
      <p>
        It depends on the weight. Finals worth 30–40% can significantly change
        your overall grade.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can a final raise your grade?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. If your final exam score is higher than your current grade, it will
        raise your average.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can a final lower your grade?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. If your final exam score is lower than your current average, it will
        bring your grade down.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</GuideLayout>